goals.question: What is the relationship between Github activity and day of the week?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='time', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of Github activity over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day_of_week'] = pd.Categorical(data['day_of_week'], categories=['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday', 'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday', 'Sunday'], ordered=True)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="day_of_week", y="count", data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Github activity by day of the week?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('day').mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='day', y='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average Github activity per day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
